Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.40,0:00:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As times change, difficult cases\Nwill increase in number!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.49,0:00:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi's finally back today!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.74,0:00:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But something's not quite right!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.74,0:00:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single truth\Nfor what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.54,0:00:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.05,0:00:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.16,0:01:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A high school detective from Kansai,\NHattori Heiji, suddenly appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.29,0:01:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems he wants to\Nchallenge me, Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.63,0:01:58.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just then, a diplomat's\Nwife showed up
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.68,0:02:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and asked for a background\Ncheck of her son's girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.85,0:02:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At her home, we found the diplomat\Npoisoned to death in his study!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.06,0:02:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, it was\Na locked room murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.27,0:02:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori finds evidence\Nand figures out tricks,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.82,0:02:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but my cold and the alcohol Hattori
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.36,0:02:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,gave me caused me to collapse!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.74,0:02:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's something\Nnot right about this fever!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.74,0:02:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something's wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.00,0:02:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm burning up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.04,0:02:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My heart feels like it's gonna burst!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.50,0:02:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Kudo?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.00,0:02:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you got any problems\Nwith my theory, show yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.46,0:02:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Better hurry before I solve it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.68,0:02:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Diplomat Murder Case (Part 2).
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.60,0:02:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So who...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.10,0:02:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the killer, Hattori-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.52,0:02:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not so fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.44,0:02:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the deal, Kudo?\NForfeiting the match?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.40,0:03:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine by me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.49,0:03:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.58,0:03:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd take at least five or six minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.91,0:03:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to kill the victim\Nand pull off this trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.66,0:03:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The murder took place in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.29,0:03:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the thirty minutes between 3:30 and 4:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.75,0:03:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The doctor's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.38,0:03:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.80,0:03:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His wife is in the clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.68,0:03:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as she was with us the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.64,0:03:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Similarly, the butler is in the clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.22,0:03:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as he spoke with neighbors
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.14,0:03:34.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the whole time at the front door,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.65,0:03:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then greeted us all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.23,0:03:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where are you, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.40,0:03:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The son and girlfriend are suspicious,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.11,0:03:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since they arrived before\Nthe wife and left when we arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.70,0:03:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but they were gone\Nfor only a minute or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.33,0:03:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not enough time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.91,0:03:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0} run off to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.17,0:03:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}! Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.09,0:04:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which leaves just the old man
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.55,0:04:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who arrived after 2:00 and\Nwatched TV in the next room over!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.22,0:04:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found proof in the\NJapanese-style room...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.44,0:04:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the fishing line!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.69,0:04:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the latest and\Nstrongest type of fishing line!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.03,0:04:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a fisherman;\Ndon't pretend to play dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.03,0:04:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, on our way to this room,\Nwe ran into you at the stairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.12,0:04:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait in the\NJapanese-style room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.66,0:04:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, you were in the\NJapanese-style room after the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.50,0:04:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact this fishing line was\Nin the garbage is immutable proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.63,0:04:43.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.76,0:04:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?! Am I wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.76,0:04:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me,\Nbut has Conan-{\i1}kun {\i0}been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.43,0:04:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.60,0:04:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.64,0:04:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It was me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.65,0:04:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I win!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.98,0:05:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the one who killed my son Isao--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.20,0:05:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, I'm afraid not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.53,0:05:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.20,0:05:16.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got it all wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.12,0:05:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.71,0:05:20.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.21,0:05:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.21,0:05:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is Kudo...\NKudo Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.80,0:05:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's... It's really Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.39,0:05:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.93,0:05:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.23,0:05:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You suddenly disappear\Nand then reappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.86,0:05:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was... I was so worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.27,0:05:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit cryin, dummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.44,0:05:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gimme a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.69,0:05:47.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.49,0:05:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You show up now and say I'm wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.28,0:05:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you suggesting\Nmy theory is faulty?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.54,0:05:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.91,0:05:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.67,0:05:59.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sweating...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.17,0:06:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be over soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.50,0:06:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.84,0:06:11.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with my theory, Kudo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.06,0:06:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The trick you just explained\Nis armchair theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.73,0:06:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 100% impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.52,0:06:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Say what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.02,0:06:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Kudo-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.61,0:06:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to interrupt,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.53,0:06:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but his locked room\Ntrick works perfectly!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.94,0:06:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We even tested it\Nout with my own pants!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.41,0:06:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You take a needle-ended line,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.03,0:06:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,tape the other end to the key holder,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and put the needle end through\Nthe pants pocket from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.25,0:06:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you pull both ends\Noutside the room, lock the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.05,0:06:48.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and by pulling the needle end...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.14,0:06:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the key will enter\Nthe pocket on its own!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.81,0:06:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One last tug and the\Nline breaks free of the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.52,0:07:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, by simply winding it up,\Nthe evidence disappears
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.65,0:07:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and creates a locked room!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.15,0:07:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the key really in your pocket,\NInspector Megure?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.99,0:07:16.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the key was in a\Ndouble pocket in the victim's pants...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.29,0:07:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.49,0:07:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.45,0:07:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you think we're lying,\Nsee for yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.41,0:07:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See?! It's in his double--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.13,0:07:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That... can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.01,0:07:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I put the line\Nthrough his double pocket!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.01,0:07:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was because Inspector Megure\Nwas sitting when you put the key in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.76,0:07:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.22,0:07:39.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he was sitting,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.60,0:07:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the pocket folded\Nand blocked the key's path,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.85,0:07:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the tape came off before\Nit could get into the double pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.11,0:07:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus the victim was heavyset,\Njust like Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.82,0:07:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.62,0:07:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when I put my hand\Nin the victim's pocket...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.70,0:08:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, his pants are tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.58,0:08:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it could happen 1 in\N10,000-- no, 1 in 10 times!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.17,0:08:08.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The result would always be the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.67,0:08:15.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Recall the key's direction when\Nit was in the victim's double pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.14,0:08:17.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The key's direction?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.85,0:08:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Even if it did get in his\Ndouble pocket 1 in 10,000 times,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.40,0:08:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would only be the key holder.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.86,0:08:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The key couldn't possibly flip over\Nto join the key holder in the pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.07,0:08:36.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact the key was fully inside
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.28,0:08:42.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,means the killer put it in\Nthe double pocket beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.21,0:08:47.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about this\Nneedle-ended fishing line I found?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.29,0:08:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another trap set by the killer\Nto place the blame on the old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.92,0:08:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found a handful of\Nothers all throughout the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.97,0:09:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer planted\Nthem in other rooms, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.93,0:09:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that it wouldn't matter where\Nthe old man was during the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.98,0:09:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he admitted to the crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.15,0:09:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He simply stepped\Ninto the killer's trap, knowingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.70,0:09:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I don't know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.95,0:09:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This room was completely locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.04,0:09:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not suggesting it was suicide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.12,0:09:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it wasn't suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.87,0:09:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus the killer's real trick is still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.75,0:09:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Real trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.76,0:09:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you forgotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.42,0:09:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you discovered the victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.38,0:09:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an opera was playing in the room
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.14,0:09:40.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there were books\Nstacked next to the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.01,0:09:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The opera was to drown out\Nthe victim's possible screams
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.60,0:09:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after being poisoned with the needle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.14,0:09:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The books were to hide\Nhis possibly-contorted face.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.73,0:09:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.74,0:09:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose eyes and ears\Nneeded to be fooled?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.99,0:10:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori... Yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.74,0:10:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.29,0:10:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not just you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.08,0:10:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None of the others who came\Nin with you noticed, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.00,0:10:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you don't mean--!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.13,0:10:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you entered the study,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.09,0:10:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the first one to approach the victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.43,0:10:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! The killer... was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.39,0:10:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.32,0:10:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! The killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.82,0:10:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was you, Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.49,0:10:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She killed her husband?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.78,0:10:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.62,0:10:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean the victim\Nwas still alive then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.37,0:10:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She had only knocked\Nhim out with drugs or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.88,0:10:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then she poisoned him with the\Nneedle when pretending to wake him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.88,0:10:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was only natural\Nthat no one noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.88,0:11:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the sleeping drug and the\Npoison were both powerful enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.26,0:11:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the victim would die immediately\Nafter being pricked, as if asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.77,0:11:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She set up the opera\Nand the books just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.65,0:11:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if this sleeping\Ndrug turned up in an autopsy,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.19,0:11:19.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this trick would've...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.07,0:11:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we wouldn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.16,0:11:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We assumed he was\Ndead before we entered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.74,0:11:29.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We only would've known he\Nwas knocked out before he was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.79,0:11:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this was a\Npsychological locked room murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.04,0:11:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,based on our assumption that\Nno one would ever invite a detective
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.59,0:11:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to a locked room\Nand then kill someone in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.30,0:11:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That what you wanna say, Kudo?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.09,0:11:45.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.47,0:11:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's see some proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.06,0:11:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, I didn't see her\Npull out a poisoned needle!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.31,0:11:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She took out the needle
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.36,0:12:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in a way that\Nno one would notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.28,0:12:02.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Together with her key!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.74,0:12:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Her key?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.57,0:12:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Her key holder is of\Nthe same design as the victim's.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.12,0:12:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally,\Nhers should also split in two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.92,0:12:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.34,0:12:22.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,please show us your key and\Nthe inside of your key holder!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.13,0:12:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't mind, Madam...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.73,0:12:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is this groove?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.10,0:12:36.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The poison needle was\Nlikely stored in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.94,0:12:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She customized it so she could pull\Nit out right after entering the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.82,0:12:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, that very key holder
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.91,0:12:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is definitive proof\Nthat she is the killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.54,0:12:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would she kill her husband?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.71,0:12:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If my hunch is correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.75,0:13:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,her motive is in this photograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.72,0:13:05.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is from when\Nshe was still young...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.01,0:13:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look closer, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.85,0:13:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't she look like someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.81,0:13:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She looks just like Yukiko-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.02,0:13:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's absurd!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.35,0:13:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? Only her\Nhair is a different color!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.06,0:13:20.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course she looks like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.94,0:13:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm... Yukiko's mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.20,0:13:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.11,0:13:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.24,0:13:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.70,0:13:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you had her\Nwith your husband, Isao-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.37,0:13:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Yukiko is my daughter\Nfrom my previous marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.21,0:13:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! She's the daughter of\NYamashiro Kenji, a diplomat outcast
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.84,0:13:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from society by my current husband\NTsujimura Isao twenty years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.43,0:13:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yamashiro Kenji?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.22,0:13:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the man who died\Nin prison twenty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.77,0:13:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsujimura's goal was to get rid of him,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.52,0:13:59.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since he was a rival diplomat!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.06,0:14:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then to obtain me as his wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.98,0:14:06.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband was arrested,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.65,0:14:09.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Yukiko was adopted by his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.28,0:14:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having hit rock bottom mentally,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.74,0:14:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I broke up with my wife just for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.75,0:14:20.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsujimura cajoled me,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.67,0:14:24.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I wound up\Nwife to that devilish man!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.30,0:14:31.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I realized it all when Takayoshi-{\i1}san\N{\i0}brought home a photo of Yukiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.43,0:14:36.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I thought it was just an\Nuncanny resemblance, but Tsujimura...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.39,0:14:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never! I refuse to let him\Nbe with the daughter of that man!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.07,0:14:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shocked, I continued to press him,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.99,0:14:52.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he started to talk about how\Nhe framed Yamashiro for corruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.62,0:14:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that his father had assisted with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.91,0:15:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Kimie-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.21,0:15:03.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't thinking\Nstraight back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.04,0:15:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.71,0:15:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You purposely took her bait\Nto try to make up for your past...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.10,0:15:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no use in\Npretending to be good, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.64,0:15:23.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he left this life as\Nan innocent man who was framed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.74,0:15:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takayoshi-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.94,0:15:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.16,0:15:36.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'm not fit to say this now,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.08,0:15:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but please take care of Yukiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.87,0:15:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.46,0:15:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah. So she was\Nharsh with her daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.59,0:15:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that she wouldn't realize.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.18,0:15:53.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.68,0:15:53.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.47,0:15:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.51,0:15:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Shinichi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.76,0:15:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's just my cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.52,0:16:04.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how'd you know all\Nthose details about the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.15,0:16:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had to have\Nbeen spying from nearby...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.77,0:16:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get real. That kid with the\Nglasses told me on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.65,0:16:12.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.86,0:16:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.03,0:16:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Said there was a weird detective\Nfrom Osaka and to come right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.37,0:16:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-S-So I finished up the case\NI was on, hopped on a train--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.88,0:16:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.88,0:16:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me it's weird that you\Ndon't ask how I am on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.13,0:16:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were actually\Nnearby, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.59,0:16:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you were watching\Nhow worried I was and laughing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.81,0:16:41.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.02,0:16:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.89,0:16:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm this... this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.19,0:16:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't underestimate me, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.82,0:16:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.99,0:16:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell plenty\Njust from your voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.74,0:17:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi! Hold on!\NI'll go get the doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.92,0:17:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So my reasoning was\Nwrong from the very start...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.42,0:17:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lose in every which way this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.47,0:17:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're good, Kudo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.88,0:17:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your logic's one level above mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.43,0:17:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.47,0:17:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no winning, losing, above,\Nor below when it comes to logic...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.10,0:17:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all...\Nthere's always only one truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.24,0:17:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.91,0:17:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I was so focused\Non our match that I lost my cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.33,0:17:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kudo!\NAre you sure it's just a cold?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.79,0:17:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.92,0:17:51.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kudo! You alright?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.59,0:17:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.84,0:17:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-Not good...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.18,0:17:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.76,0:17:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My heart again!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.81,0:18:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm burning up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.73,0:18:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like my bones are melting!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.19,0:18:09.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.82,0:18:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me I'm turning back...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.61,0:18:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After I finally returned to normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.32,0:18:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I turning back into that kid...\Ninto Conan again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.45,0:18:24.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.29,0:18:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.00,0:18:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know you shouldn't\Nbe moving around!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.29,0:18:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! If I turn into Conan now,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.92,0:18:36.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran will discover my identity...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.63,0:18:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.93,0:18:47.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just his coat! Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.39,0:18:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please! Don't make me turn back!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.65,0:18:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least let me tell Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.19,0:18:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.57,0:18:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...with my real mouth
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.94,0:18:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and my real voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.28,0:19:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...just one last thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.16,0:19:10.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.38,0:19:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From in there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.75,0:19:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.88,0:19:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.05,0:19:27.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where were you?! I looked all over!\NAnd where'd you get that shirt?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.43,0:19:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I was all sweaty,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.85,0:19:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I borrowed this from that room...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.10,0:19:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, have you seen Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.73,0:19:39.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi-{\i1}niichan {\i0}said he\Nremembered a new case and...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.45,0:19:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.07,0:19:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He changed clothes\Nand went out the front door.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.03,0:19:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.03,0:19:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he also said not to tell\Nanyone he was involved with this case...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.34,0:19:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.63,0:20:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.06,0:21:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, I was in\Nbed for three days straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.35,0:21:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During that time,\NHattori Heiji went back to Osaka,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.11,0:21:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and thanks to my request\Nto Ran right before I fainted,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.15,0:21:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo Shinichi's name\Ndidn't appear in the papers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.70,0:21:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now the men in black who\Nshrunk me won't find out I'm alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.00,0:21:59.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how did I turn back\Ninto my high school form?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.59,0:22:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute! As I recall,\Nhe showed up, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.80,0:22:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then I drank that\Nalcohol he brought!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.35,0:22:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.69,0:22:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's gotta be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.19,0:22:20.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I turned back by drinking that alcohol!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.23,0:22:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! There's still a lot left!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.78,0:22:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One drink caused that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.65,0:22:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I drink this all,\NI can turn back completely!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.78,0:22:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.99,0:22:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you drinking, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.83,0:22:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought! Alcohol!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.21,0:22:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know kids aren't\Nsupposed to drink alcohol!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.88,0:22:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid!\NI'm a 2nd-year high schooler!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.72,0:22:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, that's still underage...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.93,0:22:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry and change your clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.80,0:22:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.93,0:22:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your friends are here!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.31,0:22:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.64,0:22:58.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.81,0:22:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.90,0:23:02.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not you guys again...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.27,0:23:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were so worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.23,0:23:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were sick for three days!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.74,0:23:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so lucky you could skip school.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.03,0:23:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll catch a cold, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.57,0:23:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never catch a cold, Genta-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.25,0:23:15.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.09,0:23:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like they say,\N"Stupid people don't catch--"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.58,0:23:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's good that you're\Nback to normal now!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.90,0:23:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I'm back to how I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.21,0:23:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why do we have\Nto go to the library now?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.41,0:23:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only one who hasn't\Nturned in a book report for class!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.19,0:23:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we figured we'd help you out! Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.91,0:23:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.91,0:23:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.58,0:23:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever. Genta and Mitsuhiko\Nare just sticking with Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.33,0:23:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess I should go with 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.69,0:23:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once I drink that alcohol and\Nturn back into a high school student,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.92,0:23:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I might never get to\Nhang out with them again...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.61,0:24:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, Tamada-{\i1}san {\i0}has\Nbeen missing since two nights ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.32,0:24:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-Idiot! Don't turn the lights on!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.08,0:24:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! I know where\Nthe body is hidden!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.10,0:24:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.45,0:24:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Library Murder Case."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.84,0:24:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.98,0:24:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Backwards Book.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.65,0:24:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is next episode Conan's last case?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.79,0:24:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective Boys are immortal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.89,0:24:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
